#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:3 a8a5b4ea4d7543aab77769b63fdadf06
msgid "Glossary"
msgstr "Glossaire"

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:6 782c16b3031742139cbdda76ff39a648
msgid "admin qube"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:8 5d01ec7542ae4b4d8b1e901c9894c4e2
msgid "A type of :term:`qube` used for administering Qubes OS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:10 6fc01e734fec4830a090f2e60730d9cd
msgid "Currently, the only admin qube is :term:`dom0`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:13 7df9a923c3b348b49f908e6e409f0ce2
msgid "app qube"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:15 feb160a31096497a81db1b87948048b2
msgid ""
"Any :term:`qube` that does not have a root filesystem of its own. Every app "
"qube is based on a :term:`template` from which it borrows the root "
"filesystem."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:17 450492f6912d44d3b6915504d4b6fda3
msgid "Previously known as: ``AppVM``, ``TemplateBasedVM``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:19 f51bde4dfe714ed7a5f07ae059c8a789
msgid ""
"Historical note: This term originally meant “a qube intended for running "
"user software applications” (hence the name “app”)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:22 adc975db91b34ad789597c6c3ca9b6a0
msgid "disposable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:24 ae5800a718c4429c989c0d2eac1dddb1
msgid ""
"A type of temporary :term:`app qube` that self-destructs when its "
"originating window closes. Each disposable is based on a :term:`disposable "
"template`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:26 e4052d8334d747d7bc9a4c0922b27d3a
msgid "See :doc:`/user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-disposables`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:28 7955d5b0db50428db6d80b17118eb879
msgid "Previously known as: ``DisposableVM``, ``DispVM``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:31 945a4c877fcf4d3785ffbe180c4203ed
msgid "disposable template"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:33 8ec76bb576de409d89faa57bbbd28396
msgid ""
"Any :term:`app qube` on which :term:`disposable` are based. A disposable "
"template shares its user directories (and, indirectly, the root filesystem "
"of the regular :term:`template` on which it is based) with all "
":term:`disposable` based on it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:35 b14324b385dc4368acaa0a58a18e9239
msgid ""
"Not to be confused with the concept of a regular :term:`template` that is "
"itself disposable, which does not exist in Qubes OS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:37 14f50134a256499b802c6ef880ea44b4
msgid ""
"Disposable templates must be app qubes. They cannot be regular "
":term:`template`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:39 dddfa34a5ef642868ac358e9670b2676
msgid ""
"Every :term:`disposable` is based on a disposable template, which is in turn"
" based on a regular :term:`template`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:41 000acfdd583f44cbac8deb30474327ef
msgid ""
"Unlike :term:`disposable`, disposable templates have the persistence "
"properties of normal :term:`app qube`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:43 f8a5fc434a6f4e00b56b10bdb8779acd
msgid ""
"Previously known as: ``DisposableVM Template``, ``DVM Template``, ``DVM``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:46 7b8162ee240d470580cf47291dab3c3a
msgid "dom0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:48 c7d1f145fa0343ce8d6ee3863130e9ef
msgid ""
":term:`domain` zero. A type of :term:`admin qube`. Also known as the "
"**host** domain, dom0 is the initial qube started by the Xen hypervisor on "
"boot. Dom0 runs the Xen management toolstack and has special privileges "
"relative to other domains, such as direct access to most hardware."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:50 cfab333c113448b29c980c204feeac5d
msgid ""
"The term “dom0” is a common noun and should follow the capitalization rules "
"of common nouns."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:53 55393f368f144967a6ef91de6284cfb1
msgid "domain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:55 23aac51608f24ba0b0f2fdab29e26bd5
msgid "In Xen, a synonym for :term:`vm`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:57 4769b12ca3e844f499028978eb73b300
msgid ""
"See `“domain” on the Xen Wiki <https://wiki.xenproject.org/wiki/Domain>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:59 ae4f87ca15294969aa8116520514818a
msgid "This term has no official meaning in Qubes OS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:62 a723ac2c3f4b4ede822ff86b37ee934a
msgid "domU"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:64 0702e3b5cb7d4008b5b361a85ebaa9f8
msgid ""
"Unprivileged :term:`domain`. Also known as **guest** domains, domUs are the "
"counterparts to dom0. In Xen, all VMs except dom0 are domUs. By default, "
"most domUs lack direct hardware access."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:66 1b86badd97584a2a9039449871bb3b3c
msgid ""
"The term “domU” is a common noun and should follow the capitalization rules "
"of common nouns."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:68 2642bfc80da64914be360555155a8f42
msgid ""
"Sometimes the term :term:`vm` is used as a synonym for domU. This is "
"technically inaccurate, as :term:`dom0` is also a VM in Xen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:71 633298fd5cc64a4f8cd3932502b33dcc
msgid "firmware"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:73 56fbb7654f7c483e94fffb6108ed39bd
msgid ""
"Software that runs outside the control of the operating system. Some "
"firmware executes on the same CPU cores as Qubes OS does, but all computers "
"have many additional processors that the operating system does not run on, "
"and these computers also run firmware."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:74 1d4a31a9ef30451da8a696dfc793146e
msgid "HVM"
msgstr "MVM"

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:76 aa3999f0ac11436f914c70e70ec9c9cc
msgid ""
"Hardware-assisted Virtual Machine. Any fully virtualized, or hardware-"
"assisted, :term:`vm` utilizing the virtualization extensions of the host "
"CPU. Although HVMs are typically slower than paravirtualized qubes due to "
"the required emulation, HVMs allow the user to create domains based on any "
"operating system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:78 ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:141
#: b5c054c56f6a4aa6beb018091fc1e941 e89f9297210a4fb19a533a786fc8f101
msgid "See :doc:`/user/advanced-topics/standalones-and-hvms`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:79 3d0e9d376a354e70bf04277a5ae20c5c
msgid "management qube"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:81 8e0dd661e6b84465bea2a92dd6fd5cfd
msgid ""
"A :term:`qube` used for automated management of a Qubes OS installation via "
":doc:`/user/advanced-topics/salt`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:82 50576da0ca884e688376f7839427f414
msgid "named disposable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:84 8e3c74928b0d4984b08da11fe2f8472d
msgid ""
"A type of :term:`disposable` given a permanent name that continues to exist "
"even after it is shut down and can be restarted again. Like a regular "
":term:`disposable`, a named disposable has no persistent state: Any changes "
"made are lost when it is shut down."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:86 a87220eb7e254c8da9bf2961ef29e64a
msgid "Only one instance of a named disposable can run at a time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:88 abf3b15e4ca143d0a7aea21c80ea98e0
msgid ""
"Like a regular :term:`disposable`, a named disposable always has the same "
"state when it starts, namely that of the :term:`disposable template` on "
"which it is based."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:90 d2babfb61ca04bad99dcd388c466c544
msgid ""
"Technical note: Named disposables are useful for certain :term:`service "
"qube`, where the combination of persistent device assignment and ephemeral "
"qube state is desirable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:93 c272b66986d943c181c1093e2a597093
msgid "net qube"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:95 2563242bc9df487bb8a0185ccee77328
msgid ""
"Internally known as :term:`qube` that specifies from which qube, if any, it "
"receives network access. Despite the name, “net qube” (or :term:`app qube` "
"to be the :term:`service qube` ``sys-firewall``, which in turn uses ``sys-"
"net`` as its net qube."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:97 fe0f2e8e4d2542d68da8dc90d1d741ae
msgid ""
"If a qube does not have a net qube (i.e., its ``netvm`` is set to ``None``),"
" then that qube is offline. It is disconnected from all networking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:99 49619f6330b34753ba9fad3a6fa10fb9
msgid ""
"The name :term:`service qube` called a “NetVM.” The name of the ``netvm`` "
"property is a holdover from that era."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:102 6aa10797eb2045f9a8c76b1f9c27db5e
msgid "policies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:104 b73982877ffd45289f1899a55f176d16
msgid ""
"In Qubes OS, “policies” govern interactions between qubes, powered by "
":doc:`Qubes’ qrexec system </developer/services/qrexec>`. A single policy is"
" a rule applied to a qube or set of qubes, that governs how and when "
"information or assets may be shared with other qubes. An example is the "
"rules governing how files can be copied between qubes. Policy rules are "
"grouped together in files under ``/etc/qubes/policy.d`` Policies are an "
"important part of what makes Qubes OS special."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:109 67518e5f2c614fb997bee3d7feee3688
msgid "qube"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:111 871a9fd5dc4e4e68ba741b1c5a1e3f59
msgid ""
"A secure compartment in Qubes OS. Currently, qubes are implemented as Xen "
":term:`vm`, but Qubes OS is independent of its underlying "
"compartmentalization technology. VMs could be replaced with a different "
"technology, and qubes would still be called “qubes.”"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:113 7911de022a284599be8255ad05680fa6
msgid ""
"**Important:** The term “qube” is a common noun and should follow the "
"capitalization rules of common nouns. For example, “I have three qubes” is "
"correct, while “I have three Qubes” is incorrect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:115 ef169f451e8346839f9043727153c444
msgid ""
"Note that starting a sentence with the plural of “qube” (i.e., “Qubes…”) can"
" be ambiguous, since it may not be clear whether the referent is a plurality"
" of qubes or :term:`Qubes OS`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:117 bb3ef686791549febd8b77db68d6ae87
msgid ""
"Example usage: “In Qubes OS, you do your banking in your ‘banking’ qube and "
"your web surfing in your ‘untrusted’ qube. That way, if your ‘untrusted’ "
"qube is compromised, your banking activities will remain secure.”"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:119 186b6ad8b57f441da5e1325cb0de1a0b
msgid ""
"Historical note: The term “qube” was originally invented as an alternative "
"to “VM” intended to make it easier for less technical users to understand "
"Qubes OS and learn how to use it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:122 f7babcaac5314ab0a3f5ad91befcbaa2
msgid "Qubes OS"
msgstr "Qubes OS"

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:124 e0b253cf094b411a8450b4fe6fcb0c1c
msgid ""
"A security-oriented operating system (OS). The main principle of Qubes OS is"
" security by compartmentalization (or isolation), in which activities are "
"compartmentalized (or isolated) in separate :term:`qube`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:126 dd31a045ead446b0a36b685469ed8be1
msgid ""
"**Important:** The official name is “Qubes OS” (note the capitalization and "
"the space between “Qubes” and “OS”). In casual conversation, this is often "
"shortened to “Qubes.” Only in technical contexts where spaces are not "
"permitted (e.g., in usernames) may the space be omitted, as in ``@QubesOS``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:129 a71288dd14314d269d333746df2310ec
msgid "Qubes Windows Tools (QWT)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:131 426148785ccc4e40ba1af58a18f5869d
msgid ""
"A set of programs and drivers that provide integration of Windows qubes with"
" the rest of the Qubes OS system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:133 3f9842b2ad9649a4bbc4ebbdf47abba9
msgid ""
"See :doc:`/user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools` and "
":doc:`/user/templates/windows/qubes-windows`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:134 d615d87faddb45ee8fe527200faeda28
msgid "service qube"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:136 8f2edb4daf41472c9b0781208eb936a8
msgid ""
"Any :term:`app qube` the primary purpose of which is to provide services to "
"other qubes. ``sys-net`` and ``sys-firewall`` are examples of service qubes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:137 a386522d2f6f44458433c4f0f595409e
msgid "standalone"
msgstr "autonome"

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:139 bb626c763e174168bc40e967c897e4dd
msgid ""
"Any :term:`qube` that has its own root filesystem and does not share it with"
" another qube. Distinct from both :term:`template` and :term:`app qube`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:143 2a2f9dcbeded4dc8aa0b29934a0cba05
msgid "Previously known as: ``StandaloneVM``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:146 044e9c2515d84678aa0849097089fd26
msgid "template"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:148 65f8b22bc4834a30903fac494c01a57f
msgid ""
"Any :term:`qube` that shares its root filesystem with another qube. A qube "
"that is borrowing a template’s root filesystem is known as an :term:`app "
"qube` and is said to be “based on” the template. Templates are intended for "
"installing and updating software applications, but not for running them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:150 9b98c241904546abafe49980954f2a8d
msgid "See :doc:`/user/templates/templates`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:152 35f5226b8ca745baa8f245cbbe7caa40
msgid "No template is an :term:`app qube`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:154 2dbc6909511f4c789a13701963a7e1ae
msgid "A template cannot be based on another template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:156 df70ffd5ab204d638182023e5c84c8b7
msgid ""
"Regular templates cannot function as :term:`disposable template`. "
"(Disposable templates must be app qubes.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:158 d53d969f63af4a5887d2c5eb98f8155c
msgid "Previously known as: ``TemplateVM``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:161 795f1f1ac6f248a2bc5d8cffd04b501f
msgid "VM"
msgstr "MV"

#: ../../user/reference/glossary.rst:163 9e6f2967253e47d482d44ff9b2c14375
msgid ""
"An abbreviation for “virtual machine.” A software implementation of a "
"computer that provides the functionality of a physical machine."
msgstr ""
